  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN235-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. atiyamāṉ neṭumāṉañciyai auvaiyār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN235">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>ciṟiyakaṭ peṟiṉē yemakkīyu maṉṉē</l>
<l>periyakaṭ peṟiṉē</l>
<l>yāmpāṭat tāṉmakiḻn tuṇṇu maṉṉē</l>
<l>ciṟucōṟ ṟāṉu naṉipala kalattaṉ maṉṉē</l>
<l>peruñcōṟ ṟāṉu naṉipala kalattaṉ maṉṉē</l>
<l>yeṉpoṭu taṭipaṭu vaḻiyellā</l>
<l>memakkīyu maṉṉē</l>
<l>yampoṭu vēṉuḻai vaḻiyellān</l>
<l>tāṉiṟku maṉṉē</l>
<l>naranta nāṟun taṉkaiyāṟ</l>
<l>pulavunāṟu meṉṟalai taivaru maṉṉē</l>
<l>yaruntalai yirumpāṇa rakaṉmaṇṭait tuḷaiyurīi</l>
<l>yirappōr kaiyuḷum pōkip</l>
<l>purappōr puṉkaṇ pāvai cōra</l>
<l>vañcoṉuṇ ṭērccip pulavar nāviṟ</l>
<l>ceṉṟuvīḻn taṉṟava ṉaruniṟat tiṅkiya vēlē</l>
<l>yācā kentai yāṇṭuḷaṉ kollō</l>
<l>viṉippā ṭunaru millaip pāṭunark</l>
<l>koṉṟī kunaru millaip</l>
<l>paṉittuṟaip pakaṉṟai naṟaikkoṇ māmalar</l>
<l>cūṭātu vaikiyāṅkup piṟarkkoṉ</l>
<l>ṟīyātu vīyu muyirtavap palavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1"> If he obtains a little toddy, he will certainly give [it] to us. </l>
<l corresp="2"> If he obtains much toddy, </l>
<l corresp="3"> while we sing he will certainly enjoy [and] drink [it]. </l>
<l corresp="4"> As one with a little rice he will certainly have very many plates </l>
<l corresp="5"> and as one with much rice he will certainly have very many plates. </l>
<l corresp="6"> All the befalling series(?) of meat with bones </l>
<l corresp="7"> he will certainly give us. </l>
<l corresp="8"> All the series of employing the spear along with the arrow </l>
<l corresp="9"> he certainly will stand. </l>
<l corresp="10"> With his hand fragrant of bitter orange </l>
<l corresp="11"> he will certainly rub my head reeking of flesh. </l>
<l corresp="12"> Piercing a hole in the wide bowl of great bards with rare heads </l>
<l corresp="13"> going right through the hands of mendicants too, </l>
<l corresp="14"> while the sorrowful dolls of those who keep them slip down, </l>
<l corresp="15"> going into the tongue of poets with fine discrimination [and] pretty words, </l>
<l corresp="16"> it has descended, the spear that has gone deep into his precious vital spot. </l>
<l corresp="17"> [Our] father who is [our] support, where is he? </l>
<l corresp="18"> Now there are none who sing and none who give something to those who sing. </l>
<l corresp="19"> Like the big flower of the fragrant Pakaṉṟai from the dewy ghat </l>
<l corresp="20a-21"> that is kept without being worn, without giving anything to others </l>
<l corresp="22"> lives [are] very many that will perish. </l>
</lg>
